<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGHWAY PILEUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I don't understand why a 70-car pileup in the fog makes the front page (Jan. 
16). It happens so often it isn't news anymore. 
</P>
<P>
 The only thing unusual is that we have so many idiots doing it over and over, 
following one another into the fog like highway lemmings. 
</P>
<P>
 If you asked them to drive blindfolded at 60 miles per hour they would think 
you were crazy. Yet this is exactly what they do when they speed into a fog. 
</P>
<P>
 Some highways have crosses by the side of the road to indicate where a fatal 
accident has occurred. For the highway lemmings we should pile all the wrecked 
vehicles in one heap as a monument to stupidity. 
</P>
<P>
 V. FRED RAYSER 
</P>
<P>
 Yucca Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
