<HEADLINE>
<P>
TELLY SAVALAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Actor Telly Savalas is still alive on a 747 en route to New York from LAX, 
in my mind (" 'Kojak' Star Telly Savalas Dies at 70," Jan. 23). A few years 
ago, while traveling first class with his wife and new baby, Savalas' credit 
card stubbornly refused to trigger a call from the in-flight phone behind the 
cockpit.Noting his quiet frustration, I tried my credit card. It did work. So I 
turned the phone over him.  
</P>
<P>
 "Hello, Mama! It's Telly!" he gushed. I walked away. Later, when I returned to 
make a call myself, Savalas quietly extended a clenched fist. It was stuffed 
with bills. I told him I couldn't accept the cash and not to worry. 
</P>
<P>
 Kojack's final words still ring in my ears. 
</P>
<P>
 "I owe you," he said, as we parted. 
</P>
<P>
 ROB MACK 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
