</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Port Hueneme dentist has been named president of the Port Hueneme Chamber of 
Commerce, officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert E. Turner, who owns a dental practice on Pleasant Valley Road, will 
lead the city's Chamber of Commerce for a one-year term, said Pat Zanuzoski, 
the business group's executive manager. 
</P>
<P>
 Turner was installed during a dinner Wednesday at the Mandalay Beach Resort in 
Oxnard. Brady Cherry, director of Port Hueneme's recreation and community 
services department, was named citizen of the year at the same dinner. 
</P>
<P>
 Cherry received the honor because he has shown "social responsibility" for the 
residents of Port Hueneme during the five years he has worked for the city, 
Zanuzoski said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cherry established the city's senior appreciation day, when senior volunteers 
are treated to a hot meal and given awards, Zanuzoski said. Cherry spends his 
own money to pay for the parties, Zanuzoski added. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
