WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; APPLICANTS SOUGHT FOR PARK BOARD VACANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK McCARTNEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pleasant Valley Recreation and Park District is seeking applicants to 
finish a portion of the term of a director who resigned. 
</P>
<P>
 John D. Dell'Amico resigned Jan. 12 with nearly three years left on his 
four-year term, citing personal reasons and frustration over the district's 
inability to complete more projects. 
</P>
<P>
 Dell'Amico, 61, said he plans to move to the Northern California community of 
Mt. Shasta. 
</P>
<P>
 "Camarillo was a sleepy little town of 8,000 when I moved here in 1961," he 
said. "Now it's getting too congested." 
</P>
<P>
 Dell'Amico was elected to the district's board of directors in 1984 and 
reelected twice. 
</P>
<P>
 The district is seeking a qualified applicant to replace Dell'Amico until 
November, when an election will be held for a replacement to serve the 
remaining two years, said Eldred Lokker, the district's general manager. 
</P>
<P>
 An applicant must be an eligible voter who lives in or owns property in the 
park district. Applicants should submit a letter of interest, along with a 
resume and other pertinent information, to the board of directors by Feb. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications may be sent to the Pleasant Valley Recreation and Park District, 
Camarillo Community Center, 1605 E. Burnley St., Camarillo 93010. PATRICK 
McCARTNEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
