EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; MAN ARRESTED IN SUSPECTED DRUG SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's deputies and agents from the FBI arrested a Moorpark 
man for allegedly dealing in marijuana out of his apartment, Sheriff's Sgt. 
Gary Pentis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Siamak Salehi, 28, was arrested Thursday afternoon after a two-week 
surveillance by officers who reported witnessing several drug buys, Pentis 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Along with Salehi, sheriff's deputies arrested three other people seen 
purchasing drugs, Pentis said. Enrique Castaneda, 29; Amber Tanner, 18, and 
Jose Lopez, 18, all of Thousand Oaks, were cited on possession of marijuana and 
released, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Upon searching Salehi's apartment, detectives discovered about 12 pounds of 
marijuana with an estimated street value of $36,000, a small quantity of 
psilocybin mushrooms and anabolic steroids, Pentis said. Detectives also 
reported finding a .38-caliber handgun. 
</P>
<P>
 Salehi, a convicted felon, was booked at the County Jail on suspicion of 
selling marijuana, illegal possession of dangerous drugs and felony possession 
of a handgun, Pentis said. Salehi's bail is set at $20,000. SCOTT HADLY 
