<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / PACIFIC 10 ROUNDUP; STOUDAMIRE LIFTS ARIZONA OVER OREGON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Damon Stoudamire said that all he did to break out of a two-game scoring slump 
was return to basics. 
</P>
<P>
 It paid off in a 27-point performance Thursday night, helping 13th-ranked 
Arizona defeat Oregon, 98-86, at Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Stoudamire came in with a 17.6-point average but had scored only nine points 
against UCLA and four against USC last week. 
</P>
<P>
 "I worked hard, played hard and stuck around after practice," he said. He took 
extra shots and concentrated on "doing the basics to get back to the way I 
was." 
</P>
<P>
 He scored 18 first-half points, including three three-point baskets, but after 
making two more three-point shots in the first 3:29 of the second period, 
Stoudamire went scoreless for 14:22. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona, 15-3 overall and 4-2 in the Pacific 10 Conference, made 26 of 38 free 
throws; Oregon (6-9, 2-4) made nine of 13. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona State 88, Oregon State 82 -- Stevin Smith scored a career-high 39 
points and tied his own Pac-10 record by making 10 three-point shots to lead 
the Sun Devils (9-6, 4-2) at Tempe, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona State made 76.9% of its shots in the first half as Smith made seven of 
eight three-point shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Kareem Anderson led Oregon State (5-10, 1-5) with 24 points. 
</P>
