<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; PACIFICA RACES PAST BOLSA GRANDE, 84-72 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacifica Coach Bob Becker's up-tempo style must be growing on Garden Grove 
League fans because a packed gymnasium watched the host Mariners run and gun 
past Bolsa Grande, 84-72, Thursday at Pacifica High. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica (18-1, 9-0 in league), ranked seventh in the county, used its 
pressure defense to force 20 turnovers, and Chris Vlasic scored 22 of his 27 
points in the second half to help the Mariners hold off the stubborn Matadors 
(9-10, 5-4). 
</P>
<P>
 "I think they just ran out of gas," Becker said. "We've been playing nine and 
10 guys all year and I think we wore them down. We had a little more left in 
the tank." 
</P>
<P>
 Although Pacifica opened the second quarter scoring seven points in 25 
seconds, then started the third quarter with a 12-2 run, the Mariners were 
never safely ahead until Ramon Alliman, who had 13 points, came up with a steal 
followed by a two-handed dunk, which brought the crowd to its feet and gave 
Pacifica a 78-63 lead with five minutes remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Baughman had 18 points and 14 rebounds and Tuan Pham had 18 points, 
including four three-pointers, to keep the Matadors close. Bolsa Grande 
trailed, 42-40, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 "I told our kids at halftime, 'We're close, but we are not where we want to 
be,' " Bolsa Grande Coach Tom Cardoza said. "We wanted a game in the 60s. But 
they have some outstanding athletes, they're strong inside, they can shoot 
three-pointers . . . you can't defend everybody." 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande had problems with Vlasic, who scored Pacifica's first 10 points 
of the third quarter in a two-minute span, giving Pacifica a 52-42 lead with 5 
minutes 45 seconds remaining in the quarter. Vlasic made three of his four 
three-pointers in the third quarter, and made nine of 10 shots in the second 
half. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Pacifica jumped to a 12-point lead to start the third quarter, the 
Matadors battled back and after a three-pointer by Pham and a pair of layups by 
Baughman, Bolsa Grande cut the lead to 65-58 after three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Stewart and Cuong Doan each scored 11 points for Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
 Jon Surface and Erik Maurer each scored 10 points and Ryan Teague had three 
three-pointers for Pacifica. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
