<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; BRACKETT'S GOAL HELPS COSTA MESA TIE ESTANCIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Costa Mesa's Heather Brackett scored on a corner kick with 22 minutes 
remaining to give the Mustangs a 1-1 tie with Estancia in a Pacific Coast 
League girls' soccer game Thursday at Costa Mesa High. 
</P>
<P>
 Brackett's goal came when Estancia goalkeeper Beth Ferryman drifted into the 
goal after making an over-the-shoulder catch on the corner kick. 
</P>
<P>
 On the play, Ferryman thought the ball went out of bounds in the air before 
re-entering the field of play, but Brackett said the ball did the opposite, 
curving toward the goal causing Ferryman's momentum to carry her past the goal 
line. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a disappointing way to have a game decided," Ferryman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The game would not have been as close if it hadn't been for Mustang goalkeeper 
Sara Ackelson, who made 16 saves, many on uncontested shots from close range. 
</P>
<P>
 The defending league champion Eagles (9-5-4, 3-1-2) scored when Whitney 
Gilliam took a corner kick from Tracie Manz and scored her first goal of the 
season 15 minutes into the game. 
</P>
<P>
 For most of the game, Costa Mesa (7-2-5, 2-1-3) was backpedaling in its 
defensive zone as Estancia used an effective passing game to keep pressure on 
Ackelson. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our whole season has consisted of playing solid defense and counterpunching," 
Costa Mesa Coach Dan Johnston said. "Last season we lost a lot of games, 1-0, 
but this season our counterattack and good goalkeeping have kept us in every 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 "And this is our first winning season in the four years we've had a program." 
DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012894-0107 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 007913 </DOCID>
