<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: SCHRAFF GROUP GETS NEW ART DIRECTOR, SENIOR 
COPYWRITER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Glenda Hoffman has joined Schraff Group, a Fountain Valley advertising and 
public relations firm, as art director. She was formerly involved in graphic 
promotions for Ingram Micro Inc., a Santa Ana computer products distributor. In 
addition, Jeff Perry was appointed senior copywriter. He also worked at Ingram 
Micro and was marketing communications manager at FVC Systems & Software Inc. 
in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 * Hollon H. Bridges Jr. has been appointed vice president of sales and 
marketing for Simulation Sciences Inc., a Brea process simulation software 
supplier. Before joining the company, he was vice president for worldwide sales 
and support at Biosym, a molecular modeling software company. 
</P>
<P>
 * David William Stein has joined Imperial Trust Co. as manager of its new 
regional trust office in Orange County. Before joining the company, he was vice 
president of sales and marketing for Northern Trust Bank of California and vice 
president and manager of employee benefit trusts for Trust Services of America. 
 
</P>
<P>
 * Judy Hay has opened Career Connection, a career development service in 
Newport Beach. She has been a counselor for more than seven years at the UCI 
Extension Women's Opportunity Center.  
</P>
<P>
 * Rene H. Caron has been appointed a senior vice president of South Coast 
Communications Group, an Irvine investor relations, marketing, communications 
and public relations company. He rejoins the company after serving as vice 
president/vertical marketing operations at Alpha Microsystems in Santa Ana and 
president of Alpha Healthcare Inc., a subsidiary. 
</P>
<P>
 * Greg Miner has joined Odetics Inc., an information automation company in 
Anaheim, as chief financial officer. He succeeds Tom Juengel, who retired last 
April. Miner comes to Odetics from Laser Precision Corp. in San Juan 
Capistrano, where he had served as vice president and chief financial officer 
since 1984. Before joining Laser Precision, Miner was with the accounting firm 
Deloitte & Touche in Orange County as manager and senior accountant. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jackie Conkling has been appointed vice president, account management for 
Anderson Communications Co. Inc., a Newport Beach advertising and public 
relations agency. She has been with the firm for more than seven years, most 
recently as management supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 * Perry Cohen has been appointed president and chief operating officer of 
SysteMed Inc.'s Insurx Inc. subsidiary in Cleveland. Cohen was formerly chief 
operating officer of Aetna Pharmacy Management. SysteMed, based in Laguna 
Hills, is a manager of prescription drug benefit systems. 
</P>
<P>
 * Darius Anderson has been appointed interim executive director of the Food 4 
Less Foundation, which supports nonprofit organizations that assist children at 
risk and disadvantaged individuals. He succeeds Fred Snowden, who had held the 
position since early 1992 until his death last week. Anderson is vice 
president, governmental relations for Food 4 Less Supermarkets in La Habra. He 
had been western states finance director for the Democratic National Committee 
before joining Food 4 Less in 1993. 
</P>
