<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: POMONA; MAN LINKED TO 
PHOTOS OF MOLESTED CHILD GETS 20 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man linked to photographs of a 4-year-old molestation victim was sentenced 
Thursday to 20 years in prison for lewd conduct. As part of a plea bargain, 
however, authorities dropped child pornography charges against Paul Lynn Loe, 
46, of Rowland Heights. 
</P>
<P>
 Loe pleaded no contest earlier this month to eight charges of lewd acts on a 
child in connection with the molestation of a girl. Three additional counts 
against Loe of lewd conduct and five counts of child pornography were 
dismissed. 
</P>
<P>
 Low, the father of three, had faced a maximum sentence of 29 years if 
convicted on all counts. He was arrested in late December after pictures of a 
young girl being molested were found in a trash bin behind a Whittier hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 When a cropped version of one photo showing the victim's face appeared on 
television, the girl was identified, leading police to Loe. 
</P>
<P>
 He and his girlfriend shared a Rowland Heights apartment unit with the girl 
and her mother, and he occasionally baby-sat the child. 
</P>
