<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH; JUDGE 
BLOCKS PROPOSAL TO ERECT STREET BARRIER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Superior Court Judge on Thursday blocked Long Beach from erecting a 
controversial street barrier between an upscale housing tract and the city of 
Hawaiian Gardens. 
</P>
<P>
 The fence -- which would have blocked off Pioneer Boulevard at the border of 
Hawaiian Gardens and the El Dorado Park Estates in East Long Beach -- was 
approved by the Long Beach City Council in December.Traffic studies showed that 
the residential streets were overused, city officials said, probably by 
commuters seeking access to the San Gabriel River Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 But some neighborhood residents and Hawaiian Gardens council members protested 
and, in a suit filed Thursday, opponents alleged the gate was intended to keep 
lower-income, minority motorists out of the El Dorado area. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Diane Wayne issued a temporary restraining 
order that will remain in effect until Feb. 18, when a preliminary injunction 
hearing is scheduled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
