<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: STANTON; MAN WHO WAS HIT BY PICKUP TRUCK DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 28-year-old man who was hit by a pickup truck as he tried to cross Beach 
Boulevard died of his injuries early Thursday, the Orange County coroner's 
office said. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin Saldana of Stanton was running across Beach near Pacific Street about 
7:30 p.m. Tuesday when he was hit by the northbound truck. He was not in a 
crosswalk, Sheriff's Lt. Jay Mendez said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He had made it to the center divider but as soon as he stepped onto the other 
side, he was hit," Mendez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Saldana died at 3:10 a.m. Thursday at UCI Medical Center in Orange. The driver 
of the pickup was not cited, Mendez said. 
</P>
