<TEXT>
<P>
 McDonnell Exec Expected to Get Key CalPERS Post: The California Public 
Employees Retirement System, the nation's largest public retirement fund, is 
expected to appoint Sheryl K. Pressler as its new chief investment officer. 
Sources say CalPERS, which has about $80 billion in assets and 970,000 members, 
will announce her appointment as early as Monday. Pressler is director of 
retirement funds management at McDonnell Douglas Corp. She would replace DeWitt 
Bowman, who has held the position for five years. 
