THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended Jan. 23, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest Week Albums: 9.0 Singles: 1.4 
</P>
<P>
 Week Ago Albums: 10.1 Singles: 1.5 
</P>
<P>
 Year Ago Albums: 9.4 Singles: 1.6 Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 Insiders in the Michael Jackson camp are citing a strengthened relationship 
between the superstar and his manager, Sandy Gallin, who maintained a strong 
behind-the-scenes presence as his client battled allegations of molesting a 
13-year-old boy. Gallin, attorney John Branca and business manager Marshall 
Gelfond have emerged from the controversy as Jackson's core inner circle and 
will now spearhead efforts to resolve a lawsuit brought against Jackson by 
promoter Marcel Avram over canceled international concert dates.Insiders are 
looking for a multimillion-dollar settlement or a rescheduling of the shows. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Hits magazine is a weekly music industry trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Soundscan Inc. 
</P>
