<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: ZEIDMAN TO QUIT DISTRIBUTION POST AT MIRAMAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Miramax Films confirmed that its longtime distribution chief, Marty Zeidman, 
will leave the company soon.  
</P>
<P>
 A Miramax spokeswoman said Zeidman plans to get into other film ventures, but 
she declined to say who will replace him.However, sources confirmed reports 
that Jack Foley, who formerly headed distribution at MGM/UA, has been tapped 
for the job at the maverick film distributor, which is known for releasing such 
films as "The Crying Game" and "The Piano." 
</P>
<P>
 Zeidman has been with Miramax, which was bought last year by Walt Disney Co., 
for nearly six years. In a statement, Miramax co-Chairmen Bob and Harvey 
Weinstein praised Zeidman and said they are sorry he is leaving.  
</P>
<P>
 * Paramount Pictures' Motion Picture Group named Richard Fowkes senior vice 
president in charge of business affairs and Mark Bakshi vice president of 
feature production management. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jeffrey S. Glover has been named vice president of business affairs at 
Samuel Goldwyn Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Nostalgia Network said it removed Michael E. Marcovsky as chairman and 
chief executive, effective immediately. It named Frank Jett, company president, 
acting chief executive and Gerald P. Carmen acting chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 * Russell W. Lyster has been named president of Prism Management, a new talent 
management company formed by Prism Entertainment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
