<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Delta Air Lines Inc. lost $141 million, or $3.36 per share, on revenue of 
$3.02 billion in the quarter, the second of its fiscal year. The Atlanta-based 
carrier lost $144.4 million, or $3.46 per share, on revenue of $2.87 billion a 
year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The latest quarter included a pretax charge of $112.3 million to pay for the 
early retirement of 1,492 workers in November. 
</P>
