<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: INTERNATIONAL TRADE; WHAT IN THE WORLD YOU NEED TO KNOW AS IMPORTER 
OR EXPORTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard; Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For those who want to become successful importers or exporters, the Center for 
International Trade Development in Irvine may be the place to start. 
</P>
<P>
 Many of the more than 1,000 entrepreneurs and business executives who stopped 
by the center in the past two years had little idea how to get involved in 
global trade, said Ray Thompson, center manager. 
</P>
<P>
 At the center, students were given advice, classroom instruction and heard 
about informal get-togethers with trade experts aimed at turning an idea or 
product into an international moneymaker. 
</P>
<P>
 The center operates under the auspices of Coastline Community College in 
Fountain Valley, and is one of nine such centers around the state. Services 
include export counseling, technical assistance, strategic planning, providing 
trade finance options, resources and referrals. 
</P>
<P>
 The services are free. 
</P>
<P>
 So far, Thompson said many clients hear of the center through referrals from 
the U.S. Department of Commerce offices in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 "They will automatically refer you to me and (we'll) help you on how to get 
started," Thompson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The center can be reached at (714) 863-9356. 
</P>
</TEXT>
