</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Western Digital Corp. said Thursday it has laid off 80 employees in its 
money-losing microcomputer products division as part of an effort to make the 
division profitable. 
</P>
<P>
 The company cut 60 positions at its Irvine headquarters and 20 at a plant in 
Mountain View, said Brenda Bennett, a company spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 The cuts leave Western Digital with 6,600 employees worldwide, including 900 
in Orange County. Bennett said the affected workers will receive severance pay 
and outplacement services. 
</P>
<P>
 Western Digital reported a profit in its most recent quarter, but its 
microcomputer products division has consistently lost money. The division, 
which designs and sells chips that control a computer's internal functions, 
accounts for 15% of the company's sales. 
