<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIMI VALLEY COACH FACES DISCIPLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kathryn Scroggin, Simi Valley High principal, has made a recommendation to the 
Simi Valley Unified School District for disciplinary action against basketball 
Coach Dean Bradshaw for his shoving of a player during a game Jan. 14 against 
Westlake, sources said Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Scroggin on Thursday completed her investigation into the altercation between 
Bradshaw and senior guard Sam Rodriguez during Simi Valley's 51-44 Marmonte 
League home victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Bradshaw has been suspended from coaching the team, but has retained his 
teaching duties, pending the outcome of the investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 The severity of the recommendation is unclear, but sources indicated the 
matter will be discussed Tuesday at a school board meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Scroggin did not return phone calls Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 When contacted at home, Pioneer Athletic Director George Ragsdale declined 
comment. Ragsdale, however, did confirm the investigation has been completed 
and that the school board might rule on the situation next week. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the Simi Valley basketball team remains in turmoil. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pioneers have not played or practiced since the incident. Simi Valley 
takes the court tonight at 7:30 against Camarillo in a league game at the 
Apollo Continuation School in Simi Valley -- but without a coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Ragsdale will sit with the team, but said he will not try to coach. Instead, 
he will leave the play-calling to the team's seniors. 
</P>
