 Kaiser Permanente -- A story in Thursday's editions about new insurance 
options for members of the Kaiser Permanente health plan should have said that 
Kaiser enrollees have the option of using doctors and medical facilities 
outside the Kaiser network -- only in Southern California and only if their 
employers offer it. Throughout the state, Kaiser and Pacific Mutual Life 
Insurance Co. plan to jointly market health plans that would allow employees 
